---
import Container from "@components/Container.astro";
import Footer from "@components/Footer.astro";
import GetAppButton from "@components/GetAppButton.astro";
import Page from "@layouts/Page.astro";
---

<Page
  title="Box Timer – Free Interval Timer App for iPhone"
  description="Free interval timer app for iPhone. Set custom work time, rest time, and rounds for HIIT, CrossFit, Tabata, and boxing. No ads, no subscriptions. 4.9 stars."
  url="https://boxtimer.app/interval-timer/"
  canonical="https://boxtimer.app/interval-timer/"
>
  <Container innerClass={"flex-col items-center"}>
    <div class="w-full sm:w-9/12">
      <h1 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-sans font-bold">
        Free Interval Timer for iPhone
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl font-light text-zinc-600 mt-4">
        The simple, ad-free interval timer for HIIT, CrossFit, Tabata, and boxing rounds
      </p>

      <div class="flex justify-center mt-12 mb-16">
        <GetAppButton id="get-app-button-interval-top" />
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-sans font-bold mt-16 mb-4">
        What is an interval timer?
      </h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        An interval timer alternates between a <strong>work period</strong> and a <strong>rest period</strong>,
        repeated for a set number of rounds. It is the foundation of almost every structured training
        method — HIIT, Tabata, CrossFit EMOMs, and boxing all rely on interval timing to keep
        workouts organised and progressive.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4">
        Unlike a basic stopwatch or countdown, an interval timer handles the full workout automatically.
        Set your work time, rest time, and number of rounds once — then start the clock and focus entirely
        on training. Audio cues signal every transition so you never need to look at your phone mid-set.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-sans font-bold mt-16 mb-4">
        Why Box Timer for interval training?
      </h2>
      <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-6 space-y-3">
        <li>
          <strong>Fully customisable intervals</strong> — Set any work time, rest time, and up to
          99 rounds. From 10-second Tabata sprints to 5-minute boxing rounds.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Work-only mode</strong> — Set rest to zero for EMOM-style workouts where the
          interval itself includes your rest.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Loud audio cues</strong> — A long beep starts each work period. Three short
          warning beeps fire during the final seconds of rest so you are always ready to go.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Large, readable display</strong> — Clearly shows the current round number, time
          remaining, and whether you are in a work or rest period. Rotate to landscape for a
          full-screen view.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Works with your music</strong> — Interval beeps play alongside your playlist
          without cutting the audio.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Saved interval presets</strong> — Every completed session is stored in history.
          Name and pin your most-used interval setups for instant recall.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Free, no ads</strong> — No banners, no video ads, no subscription required.
          Every feature is available from the first launch.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-sans font-bold mt-16 mb-4">
        How to set up an interval timer
      </h2>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-outside ml-6 space-y-2">
        <li>Open Box Timer and tap <strong>Edit Timer</strong></li>
        <li>Select <strong>Interval</strong> as the timer type</li>
        <li>Set <strong>Rounds</strong> to your desired number (e.g. 8)</li>
        <li>Set <strong>Work</strong> time (e.g. 0 minutes and 30 seconds)</li>
        <li>Set <strong>Rest</strong> time (e.g. 0 minutes and 15 seconds)</li>
        <li>Turn on <strong>Countdown</strong> for a 10-second lead-in before the first round</li>
        <li>Tap <strong>Save</strong>, then <strong>Start</strong></li>
      </ol>
      <p class="mt-4">
        See the full guide:
        <a
          class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800"
          href="/support/how-to-set-an-interval-timer-with-both-work-and-rest-time/"
          >How to set an interval timer with both work and rest time</a
        >
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-sans font-bold mt-16 mb-4">
        Popular interval timer setups
      </h2>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full mt-4">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th class="text-left pb-4 pr-4 font-bold">Format</th>
              <th class="text-left pb-4 pr-4 font-bold">Work</th>
              <th class="text-left pb-4 pr-4 font-bold">Rest</th>
              <th class="text-left pb-4 font-bold">Rounds</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">Tabata</td>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">20s</td>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">10s</td>
              <td class="py-2">8</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">Classic HIIT</td>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">30s</td>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">30s</td>
              <td class="py-2">10</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">EMOM</td>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">60s</td>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">0s</td>
              <td class="py-2">10–20</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">Boxing rounds</td>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">3 min</td>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">1 min</td>
              <td class="py-2">3–12</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">Sprint intervals</td>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">20s</td>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">40s</td>
              <td class="py-2">8</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-4 text-zinc-600">
        All of these can be configured in Box Timer using the interval mode in under a minute.
      </p>

      <div class="flex justify-center mt-16 mb-8">
        <GetAppButton id="get-app-button-interval-bottom" />
      </div>

      <p class="mt-16">
        <strong>Related:</strong>
        <a class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800" href="/hiit-timer/"
          >Free HIIT Timer for iPhone</a
        >
        &nbsp;·&nbsp;
        <a class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800" href="/tabata-timer/"
          >Free Tabata Timer for iPhone</a
        >
        &nbsp;·&nbsp;
        <a class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800" href="/boxing-round-timer/"
          >Free Boxing Round Timer for iPhone</a
        >
      </p>
    </div>
  </Container>
  <Footer />
  <script type="application/ld+json">
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "HowTo",
      "name": "How to set up an interval timer on iPhone",
      "step": [
        { "@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Open Box Timer and tap Edit Timer" },
        { "@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Select Interval as the timer type" },
        { "@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Set Rounds to your desired number" },
        { "@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Set Work time (e.g. 30 seconds)" },
        { "@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Set Rest time (e.g. 15 seconds)" },
        { "@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Turn on Countdown for a 10-second lead-in" },
        { "@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Tap Save, then Start" }
      ]
    }
  </script>
</Page>
